The paper deals with multi-label classification, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of supervised learning. The paper also addresses three important real-world issues: online updating, label space dimension reduction, and cost-sensitivity. These issues are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI). However, given that the paper focuses on developing a novel algorithm for multi-label classification, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
